{
  "texts": [
    "Similarly, studying ED cases (as done by Fraser et al.",
    "48) could help determine if patients visiting the ED might have opted for primary care had they consulted an SAA beforehand.",
    "With a sample of primary care cases, the potential effect of SAAs on the redistribution of care seeking efforts could be assessed from a systems perspective.",
    "However, there may be some cases in which researchers do not want to test how SAAs perform in the real world but how they could perform in hypothetical cases, e.g., when examining if an SAA can still solve a case when another unrelated symptom is added.",
    "In such cases, artificially constructed or edited vignettes may be more helpful than representative vignettes."
  ]
}